social_posts.post_text: Just a quick reminder! Fucking up is ok! We tend to get so worked up when we fuck up!  We gotta just keep moving.  The pain the anger we can focus on that. Focus on moving forward the next move. Not ever move us a W. Ever move not taken is A L! Stop losing start winning!! If you make that move n fail it’s still a W!!! #win #fight #fyp #powerlifting

SURE HOWS THIS?? Nothing more I love then clinging and banging these keys! This is a big topic in powerlifting. Most say if u can’t do it in meets don’t? Which I agree practice how u play. But I also feel if you in the gym and are very hype and proud of what ur doing slam away. I wouldn’t make it a habit especially these bars aren’t cheap but man sometimes things just click. As athletes we should be disciplined enough to know not to do it in a meet it’s simple. I see so many negative comments when someone gets fucking fired up and slams the bar! I’m here to say fuck it up man. Have fun. That is what this all is about. Be smart but train with fun in your blood don’t worry what that ig dude will say to u. Bc odds are they have done it before. Some days I wanna break the wood in half on my platform very dumb and will cost a lot of I did but hey. We here having fun!  Also sometime that @zonesmellingsalts just hit u different! Comment your opinion let’s get weird on this Friday!

Start how finish! I see alot of lifters goofy off or not taken 1 red as serious as their top set!  I keep things simple man. If you wanna be good at something do it a lot. If you wanna buy a QB throw a football 1 million times. If you wanna learn sumo do 1 million reps. Watching videos and talking to ppl about cues is not the same as getting under the bar! Repetition is what gets you there. #FQ @fightorquitco

Are these the things I’m remembering most? FUCK NO MAN! I started this sport with 1 goal! BE THE BEST IN THE WORLD! I didn’t care what it took. Once’s I reached the top! The things I remember most are not these numbers honestly I had to look them up. 

  Am I proud that I can say I was the best in the world 1000% I was able to do things at the time I was the only 1 in the world who has done it.  To me I thought that’s what it took to be Great! Most of you say you wanna be the best but ain’t about that life! I risked double knee surgery lifting knowing I was fucking my knee up. I didn’t care bc I wanted it that bad. 

Honestly the things I remember most? Was the moments I shared with others. The people I have been able to touch and help hit that next goal! Ive helped  1,000s of people in the passed 20 years. We opened a gym and started a brand that I honestly remembering these moments over the past 3 years most! Opening a gym where anyone is welcome. Talking to each member personally I do my best to remember every single members name we have way over 100 members now. They aren’t just members to me they’re my family. They’re in OUR house. We don’t just want ppl to come in our house and not feel welcome. 

  We started running meets the way we feel meets should be run. We aren’t saying we the best. However we been in this sport for 20 years we seen alot of great and a whole alot of bad! So we try to do what feel is what the lifters will remember. Make each lifter feel special. We started with a local meet the FQ classic 1! Now it’s Become a National level meet where ppl travel all over the USA just to compete. Now we are co hosting  @the_american_pro_  which could be arguably be the biggest meet in non tested history and we added a tested day!  These are the things that I remember most. It’s always been about numbers. Just now the numbers aren’t about my personal lifting numbers. 
 
 I am very blessed for being able to do what I do. It’s been a hell of a run and I’m not stopping. Even tho I cant run bc these shitty ass knees! But ay we here!

Do you show up to gym and go right under the bar? Well stop that shit! The body needs a proper warm up. Turn on that juicy body YALL!! Here is some stuff I enjoy. @squat_university 

Here’s an excellent sumo deadlift warm up I first learned from elite powerlifter @micah_marino. 
.
This type of exercise is scientifically called “RNT” or reactive neuromuscular training. By “feeding the problem” of pulling the knees in (something we don’t want to see during the pull) the body senses the load shift & reacts - engaging the appropriate muscles to move more optimally. 
.
Science for the win.

Last Saturday! I say hey @steff_eff15 you are doing the @usapowerlifting_nv meet next weekend lol. I managed to talk her into it. She been dealing with some spine injuries! She was benching with her first up for 3 months. Didn’t deadlift or sq for 2 months. We slowly re built her up with squatting but still wasn’t pulling. 

She pulls 4 times before this meet
1st 135 for reps 
2nd time 308 for singles
3rd time 463 singles
4th 402 singles 

I told her now is the perfect time to do a usapl meet no goals for prs. No stress just do it. So that’s what she did and still had a great day! 499 dots with just showing up and having fun id say that’s pretty cool!

I am mostly proud of her for doing things she just isn’t comfortable with!

She has done 2 weeks this year with zero prep! Is this going be a thing??? Hahahahah 

Super happy and proud of you! 

It was cool seeing her have fun with the other ladies in flight A.

My name is Marino Marino and I’m addict! 

My addiction started at 15 years old. My addiction isn’t something I’m proud of. My addiction is somthing I want no young kid to do or start when I did! This shit is the real deal! Just wait please. 

My addiction is somthing that lead me to double knee surgery over 5 pec tears. Sure I have broken world records. Do I believe I could have still got to the top if I had waited yes 1000% and so can you. 

My addiction is a since saved my life! Only bc I knew I had to go train. I was so addicted to the gym I didn’t go down the road a lot of my friends and family did as a kid. 

We all have a addiction. I hope you all take the time to do ur research and stop chasing what u see on ig. Bc I can promise it don’t last for ever. All these brand you see who love you only love you when you are good that’s called business. Take your time. Talk to smart people. 

Stay natty for as long as u can. 

My story is different! And my addiction saved my life at least for 32 years it did. We can promise anything. But I can promise my addiction lead me right where I am. I’m smarter I’m healthier then I ever been. Took 15 years to understand that. I would say I am lucky. I am also addicted to giving lifters a place to have fun. 

I truly believe I will die doing this. And I will die happy! 

Thank you @elitefts this was a dream come true. If this helps 1 person my job is done. 

Mycuhhh out.

✨️ American Pro 2 ✨️
Last weekend, we made powerlifting history! The amount of support, the shares, the love...I feel all of that and I am so grateful. 

This event, each and every one of you reading this, mean everything to me. 

When powerlifting found me (over a decade ago! 👵)
I never imagined this would be the outcome. This sport literally saved my life and now I get to be a part of this forever. The American Pro is a tribute to this incredible sport that has given so much to me and to so many of you who share the same common bond. 

The American Pro would not be here if it wasn't for you, the athletes, who chose us. We put together the plan, but it's you, the athletes, who understood the assignment and brought your A-Game to our platform and made the event!

It takes a village to execute this! Thank you to our judges, managers, spotters and loaders, and media crew. From the sleepless nights working on 200+ custom graphic designs for our video walls - the meticulous work behind the scenes is nothing short of astounding. 

Our commitment is unwavering – to always prioritize our athletes and provide unforgettable experiences!

A special thank you to my partner, Micah Marino, for believing in me and coming to Virginia, just days after us talking about this crazy idea to do a Pro meet together. It's been two years now doing this thing and we are a powerhouse team because from day one, we were never afraid to go against the grain and take risks. Hard to believe we rarely see each other in person, yet we talk on the phone daily, in different time zones, for the last two years planning every detail for the American Pro! 
(I'll share more about the backstory in a future post.)

As the Vice President of the WRPF, I have never felt more proud than I do right now. We are here to show the world who we are. Looks like we have everyone's attention now! The future of powerlifting is bright! Let's keep raising the bar higher and stay tuned for an upcoming announcement for American Pro 3!

The past 3 years have been fun. Kay hired me as a coach 3 years ago. Right before the Olympia  where she bombed out. After the meet she was told to find a new coach. She also helped me with every meeet I’ve run including @the_american_pro_  all with in 3 short years. She also works a full time job and has a daughter @stormy._.lifts who we love dearly

@kr_ss is a force and ppl need to know she is the best person in this sport. No NOT ONE PERSON CAN DO WHAT SHE DOES. 

She never ask for credit bc she loves this sport and me. Sure she drives me crazy but so do half my @fightorquitco family does. That’s bc we a real family. And ppl call us bullies which is fine most don’t understand what real loyalty is. If one of us are sad we all our sad. I love that about us. 

@kr_ss im proud of you, you do what 90% of this world can’t do. It’s been a hell of a ride over the past 3 years. Thank you for giving me a chance to be a part of it. Let’s see if we can keep this train going for 3 more years.
